oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Hamby family home
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of Martha and Reuben Hamby (on right) in front of their family home. Two unidentified individuals stand nearby, behind the fence. Hamby was the owner of the sawmill and gristmill on Yellow Creek, and a store in Hebbertsburg.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: People; Houses
